  "prompt": "Why do electrons and protons attract each other?",
  "response": "Electrons and protons attract each other due to the fundamental force known as the electromagnetic force. This force arises because electrons carry a negative electric charge, while protons carry a positive electric charge. According to Coulomb's law, opposite charges attract each other, while like charges repel.\n\nThe electromagnetic force is mediated by the exchange of virtual photons, which are the force carriers in quantum electrodynamics. This attraction is a key factor in the formation of atoms, as electrons are bound to the positively charged nucleus (comprised of protons and neutrons) by this force.\n\nIn summary, the attraction between electrons and protons is due to their opposite electric charges and the electromagnetic force that acts between them.",
